{
  "stem": "1282.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it was getting worse and worse, day by day because new orders were coming down.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Evidently, Horthy did not want to allow the Jews to get out of Hungary.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He wanted to use them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the pressure from the Germans was constantly on to, to give new orders, and to expedite new restrictions or to enforce new restrictions on Jews and to the point where-- I remember, I believe it was in 1942, when we really knew that there's a problem because we were together for Seder, for the Seder eve, and I remember it so vividly that my father had the Kiddish cup in his hand, and his voice trembled.",
      "word_count": 77
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we saw tears coming down his eyes, which we never saw before, because, as I mentioned, he was a very protective person-- protected the kids from the pain of the reality.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it was obvious in that time that he was scared.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was terribly scared, and the discussion came after Kiddish of what is really going on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we insisted on knowing more, and he said to us at that time that it's not going to get any better.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's going to get worse, and he's afraid that this may be the last Passover that this family has together.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he devised a plan that in order for us to survive, we must break up the family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the only thing-- the only choice we had, is the three boys must go to different cities, each one.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "This way, some of us will survive this catastrophe.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The girls were much too young.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "This of course happened after-- also we had a very famous American going through the Carpathian area, lecturing in every town and every village.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "His name was Ze'ev Jabotinsky.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
